dsDescriptionValue.value:
This dataset includes JSON files representing the data for the now defunct New Haven Crime Log website, www.newhavencrimelog.org

The data files cover the period from January 2006 through August 2014.

The files are divided into 4 types:

  • Streets (1 file)
  • Incident types (1 file)
  • Total incident count by month (1 file)
  • incidents (1 file for each month)
    The streets and incident types are represented by keys defined in the first two files.

Example of joining the "incidents_02.json" data to a data file, such as "incidents_2011_07.json"

  • File 1: "incidents_02.json" - Definition of each incident type
  • File 2: "incidents_2011_07.json" - Crime data for July 2011
  • "pk" in File 1 == "fields.incident_type" in File 2
  • See script that opens files and checks that all data files have valid incident types: https://gist.github.com/raprasad/f7c373e14854edaacb9311e0bec8be5a

This data is derived from Excel files provided by the New Haven, CT police department as well as the use of the original Yahoo geocoder.

Data notes:

  • The geocoding was automated and is bound to contain errors.
  • Excluded from these files is:
    • Original data that did not geocode. Much of the original data may be found in other datasets within this Dataverse.
    • Crimes involving minors
